  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Male 18 years of age or older

          -  Has tumor tissue available for diagnostics

          -  Failed front line luteinizing hormone-releasing hormone analogue (LHRH) such as
             leuprolide or goserelin, or failed orchiectomy, as evidenced by disease progression.
             Patients must continue on a LHRH analogue (unless the patient had an orchiectomy)
             throughout the course of the study

          -  ECOG score of 0 or 1

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Any prior chemotherapy for prostate cancer besides hormonal therapy (including no
             prior EGFr targeting agent)

          -  Prior history of cancer other than prostate carcinoma within the past 5 years that has
             required treatment or been active (prior basal cell carcinoma is allowed)

          -  Known to be HIV positive

          -  Myocardial infarction within one year prior to entering the study
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
    <gender>Male</gender>
